1.Download and install newest version of Python2.7(Do not install 64 bit) and Scons. Please do not forget to set the environment variable of Scons
2.Creat the project using 'scons --target=mdk5 -s' using Windows CMD(please do not use shell on windows when using scons)
3.Compile the project using Keil uVision5
4.Keil uVision5 can also be used to flash and debug program.
5.If you cannot run program without any reasonable reasons, please check the following website: http://www.keil.com/support/docs/3592.htm?nsukey=EaVraFdgfI1rBNHfqNoUGM%2F89JCcMScCSR5xouA9Z7gc4CvAUkgYbsZUqMFKrmExfOzBnXZmumwesJ%2F6GnDDbxVvqc039eo5%2BZ%2Bz2aj7szXwRCVcyGnWz2gSPF1TSqKsIETf%2FfHPgCox%2FSUET9ff%2FUjCH6GbNVOjI8t397g51Vkds3q8mJNbiXy0QYEfPHJA and in "options for target->User->After Build/Rebuild->Run #1", add "$K\ARM\BIN\ELFDWT.EXE !L BASEADDRESS(0x1A000000)" if you flash program on bank a

